# Purpose: Trims the Docker build context shared by every app image.
# Why important: Keeps image builds fast and reproducible, and prevents secrets
#   (.env files) and local-only artifacts from leaking into any layer.
# Used by: apps/*/Dockerfile and infra/nginx/Dockerfile (build context is repo root).

# Dependency and build output (reinstalled/rebuilt inside the image)
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/test-results
**/playwright-report
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Mobile (Expo) local artifacts — manifest is kept so pnpm can resolve the workspace
apps/mobile/.expo
apps/mobile/android
apps/mobile/ios

# VCS, editor, logs
.git
.github
**/*.log
.vscode
.idea

# Secrets — never copy real env files into an image. Examples are allowed.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
!**/.env.prod.example
!**/.env.vps.example
